DemonicKraken (Also referred to as Demo or Demoni) is an intruder/contestant in Diary of a Tourney Kid, being a rather popular figure in the tournament community. She's the only character of the main roster to be listed as an 'Intruder' rather than 'victim', due to breaking in.

Tourney Placement[]

DemonicKraken fought You in Winners Bracket Round 1 Match 7, and lost with the votes being 51-40 ( 56% - 44% ).

DemonicKraken then fought Hamood Habibi in Losers Bracket Round 1 Match 4, and lost with the votes being 83-62 ( 57.2% - 42.8% ).

THE INTRUDER then fought THE ELEPHANT in Goners Bracket Round 1 Match 4, and won with the votes being 158–149 ( 51.5%-48.5% ),

Her current percentage is 46.1%. This is subject to change, as she is still competing.

Information[]

DemonicKraken appeared as Experiment 08-A, a Goner in progress after her execution when losing to Hamood Habibi in Losers Bracket Round 1 Match 4. Her render shows her face with a circle spiral which is a reference to Azami Kurotani's half-eaten spiral face from "Uzumaki" by Junji Itoi. Gaster's experiment log entry describes what her execution was like, where she lowered into a vortex and was presumed to be Dead. She would later make a return in Winner Round 2 Match 4's Boss track where halfway through the song she would appear and kill the imposter from Murderous Intentions and rap against You for the remainder of the track before being crushed by The Eiffel Tower.

Trivia[]

Demo's status as an intruder is because she messaged Greg near the start of the tourney to ask to specifically be character 8.

Demo would have originally been themed around capitalism/"business!", but due to overlap with Dubious Duo the murder design/route was instead chosen.

Since the DemonicKraken intentionally idenitified as bigender. Demo was often described with both masculine and feminine terms in the tournament as well, such in the QNA, with Sweetie saying "He scares me! She seems a bit... Obsessed!" in reference to her.

Some of her sources are references to DemonicKraken herself.

Her "Water and Sealife" as well as her "Unholy" source is a pun of her name. This is also why she replaced SpongeBob, who shares a water-themed sourcelist.

Her teeth source is likely a reference to "Toothland", a Discord server she's in.

Demoni's goner form is based on Uzumaki by Junji Ito, hence the horror anime goner buff. This is likely due to visual similarities to Hole Dwelling by Kikuo, a reoccurring motif of Demoni in the tournament.

Her "Psychological Horror" and her "Deceptively Dark" sources might be in reference to Doki Doki Literature Club, a game she's associated with. Her Goners design with her snapped neck is an overt reference to Natsuki's glitched out death in DDLC, with Natsuki being one of Demoni's favorite characters.

Demoni's goner form had a cameo in WR2M4, showing up in the Friday Night Funkin' mod for the boss track. She appears midway through, killing the Impostor and rapping against You for the remainder of the track.

This makes her the only goner to appear before their proper debut.

Despite having lost in Losers Round 1, Demo got a track during Losers Round 2 unlike the other LR1 Losers. This is due to her being the last character to have lost in that round meaning her experiment dual happened in Winners Round 2 and her Goner/Experiment dual occurred in Losers Round 2.

When looking at the non-Wingding text on Demo's goner sourcelist, there's a hidden message of "I NEED YOU BACK".

Demo's Match (Winners Bracket Round 1 Match 7) and Winners Bracket Round 1 Match 8 are the only matches in Winners Bracket Round 1 to be released with unique art rather than just releasing with the dual template & normal renders with the "VS!" text added.

Alongside Avery999 and KidWhom, Demo is one of the few actual Community Members to be added to DOATK.

DemonicKraken is the first character besides THE HOLY CHILD to appear in a crossover track alongside a character they faced off against.
